JToolkit Sample : Umask
=========================================================================
This sample has been provided for reference purposes only. This sample 
program is not intended to form the basis of production use.
==========================================================================
For more information on the umask, please refer “Open System Services 
User's Guide”.

==========================================================================
This java sample program illustrates setting and 
retrieving of the UMASK value.

CONTENTS OF THE DIRECTORY
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Umask.java
2. UmaskDemo.java
3. Umask.c
4. README
5. Makefile

SETUP
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Set the values of JAVA_HOME, COMP_ROOT and LINK_ROOT environment variables
in Makefile.
2. Build the Makefile
    make -f Makefile
    Successfull execution of the Makefile will generate the umask.jar and
    libumask.so file.
3. Include umask.jar file in the umask sample application directory to 
the CLASSPATH.
   example:export CLASSPATH=/usr/tandem/javaexth11/demo/umask/umask.jar
4. Include libumask.so file in the umask sample application directory to
the _RLD_LIB_PATH.
    example:export _RLD_LIB_PATH=/usr/tandem/javaexth11/demo/umask/
5. Compile the UmaskDemo.java application.
    javac UmaskDemo.java
    
EXECUTION
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Execute the UmaskDemo application.

Sample UmaskDemo java application illustrates use of the methods of Umask for
setting and retrieving the file mode creation mask.

    java  UmaskDemo
    
OUTPUT
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Current Umask = 0
New Umask  = 160

Execute 'ls -l Sample.txt' to see the file creation permission for the
Sample.txt.

-r---w-rw-    1 SUPER.SUPER      SUPER          0 Nov 13 17:08 Sample.txt

CLEAN
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Execute the below command
    make -f Makefile clean
